Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.35,0:00:24.30,Default,op,0,0,0,,Under the skies that are still unknown to me
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.30,0:00:28.37,Default,op,0,0,0,,I know, you're doing just the same -
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.37,0:00:29.98,Default,op,0,0,0,,Dreaming
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.98,0:00:35.21,Default,op,0,0,0,,Just a small glow\NFrom those great days
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.21,0:00:38.08,Default,op,0,0,0,,Is what dragging you along
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.08,0:00:41.87,Default,op,0,0,0,,Giving you faith and some comfort
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.87,0:00:45.79,Default,op,0,0,0,,Under the sun that scorches badly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.00,0:00:52.17,Default,op,0,0,0,,I only want to see your guise
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.17,0:00:53.91,Default,op,0,0,0,,But instead...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.91,0:00:59.18,Default,op,0,0,0,,I only watch \NWith tears on my face
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.18,0:01:04.74,Default,op,0,0,0,,As you slowly disappear in this noon haze
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.74,0:01:07.76,Default,op,0,0,0,,We're alone \NWe're alone
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.76,0:01:11.31,Default,op,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1000)}Walking this world on our own
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.36,0:01:16.53,Default,op,0,0,0,,{\fade(1000,0)}Looking for each other since long ago
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.53,0:01:22.49,Default,op,0,0,0,,In the end, in the end, \NAfter the day we finally meet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.49,0:01:27.00,Default,op,0,0,0,,{\b1\bord1\blur1\t(2100,2200,\shad3\blur3\c&HABADD8&)}We won't ever have to say "Goodbye"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.17,0:01:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.65,0:01:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Never say Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.23,0:01:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.99,0:01:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.20,0:01:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You too, Todo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.56,0:02:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,A scorching sun, a violent wind, and my burnt out heart\Nbecame heralds of autumn, inevitably reclaiming its rights.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.51,0:02:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only later when I started to understand \Nthis summer was nothing special in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.99,0:02:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tokyo Cup is Just a week away now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.70,0:02:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Making any progress?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.66,0:02:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Little by little.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.63,0:02:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Todo is so lucky to have left.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.92,0:02:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Still no idea when is he coming home?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.03,0:03:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.04,0:03:15.04,Default,ep title,0,0,100,,{\bord4\blur15\3c&H5C9699&\t(0,700,\bord0.11\blur0.4\3c&H6999B0&)\c&HFBFAF9&\fnGabriola\fs48\frz359.6\fscx182\fscy148}Episode 4\N\N\N\N\NTodo, I want to see you.....
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.16,0:03:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know through what, but he somehow knew for sure \Nshe will come to see him off.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.02,0:03:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when the flight was minutes away, Todo was unwilling to leave his cafe seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.37,0:03:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He was waiting for her. \NHe knew Oka is coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.71,0:03:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, she was in Coach Katsura's temple \Nwhen Todo trained there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.20,0:03:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When was the first time you noticed it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.28,0:03:48.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Had I not known about Oka and Todo for sure, \Nit would still be the most natural thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.64,0:03:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since her appearance at Nishi High, \NOka was growing fond of{/ longing for} Todo.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.61,0:03:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Todo was also not indifferent to Oka's presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.36,0:03:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka is 19, Todo is 21.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.15,0:04:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of them has each one's respective moral standards.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.00,0:04:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Whenever you grow affectionate or loving for a person, \Nno third party is allowed to interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.66,0:04:11.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, how come that both for Todo and Oka \Nthe prime moments of their lives are now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's left is to watch{ silently} from outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.92,0:04:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me, you had feelings for Oka yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.63,0:04:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So ardent, I almost got burned. \NSo undisclosed, I never dared to say a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.22,0:04:23.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But now we can just watch at them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.52,0:04:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So... He has not been it touch yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.52,0:04:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't be any other way with that fellow. \NI only coaxed him to promise coming in touch once a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.03,0:04:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At the moment, preliminary matches for the right to enter \Nthe US Open Championship are held in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.59,0:04:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,He should be taking part in those.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.07,0:04:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, though. \NThose preliminaries were supposed to end two days ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.93,0:05:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1500)}Then he certainly succeeded in preliminaries \Nand is probably busy preparing for real matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.15,0:05:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Madame Butterfly doesn't seem to know.\NAbout those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.01,0:05:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go for a swim.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.81,0:05:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, that's better! \NThen, this time try returning exactly to the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.78,0:05:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.01,0:05:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Apply more drive to the ball!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.56,0:05:37.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Your shortcoming is in the way you step!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.55,0:05:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.13,0:05:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,About 10 days have passed since then. \NHow have you been doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.73,0:05:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Was New York a welcoming place? \NFinally... Are you doing fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.58,0:05:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, it's about time you finally come in touch with me, \NI get more agitated by a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.33,0:06:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure, you will prefer to bless me with a letter \Nover anyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.82,0:06:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I look forward to it. \NBecause this will give me Todo's address in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.03,0:06:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And as soon as I know it, \NI will write you letters every single day!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.56,0:06:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As the Tokyo Cup is approaching, \Nmy special practices get tougher too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.07,0:06:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will still find time to write to you every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.79,0:06:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, there won't be a whole lot of things to write about.\NBut my heart only really trembles while I'm composing those.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.84,0:06:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Seriously...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.14,0:06:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you thinking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.34,0:07:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,40-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.78,0:07:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, rainy days won't cease in New York. Oka...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.80,0:07:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,International call, please.\NTo New York, 211...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.92,0:07:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to get in touch with New York by phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.42,0:07:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You found out what Todo's phone number is?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.46,0:07:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Not with him. \NA correspondent from my university lives there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.93,0:07:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He also knows Todo well, \Nso I asked if he has heard anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.04,0:07:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that you, master? Chiba speaks. \NHappy to hear from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.79,0:08:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There was this one match, \Nended 2 days ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.49,0:08:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.81,0:08:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.72,0:08:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi, there's a letter for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.32,0:08:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.57,0:08:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,An airmail. From New York!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.97,0:08:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi? I'll leave it down here!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.64,0:08:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.65,0:08:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.01,0:08:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,are you doing fine? \NThe rainy days seem to never cease in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.98,0:08:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I got myself a small apartment \Nalong one of the rivers{/ canals} near Central Park.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.86,0:08:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The building is old, \Nbut the area is quiet and peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.94,0:09:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,First, before I describe to you the events of the recent days, \Nthank you for coming to see me in the airport.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.37,0:09:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad we didn't have time to talk unhurriedly over dinner. \NBut I'm still happy to have seen you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.95,0:09:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The figure of you looking desperately for me \Nin this huge airport lobby will forever remain in my memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.75,0:09:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Is has become the most precious gem for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.96,0:09:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then. \NBy the time you receive this letter
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.91,0:09:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,the outcome of my first match in America \Nwill probably be already published.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.43,0:09:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I will positively win this match \Nand will then be on my way to the next goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.42,0:09:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope you do your best in the coming Tokyo Cup as well. \NThe next letter should follow soon enough. Until then...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.55,0:09:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Last ten!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.76,0:09:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.76,0:10:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Aight! Last one!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.60,0:10:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.45,0:10:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Your moves are a lot sharper than usual. \NThey radiate some kind of delight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.67,0:10:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No, there's nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.79,0:10:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What a truly eccentric buddy you are. {You truly never cease to amaze.}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.09,0:10:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all the disparate athletes I've seen,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.54,0:10:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,not a single one could manifest their state of mind \Nin the play as lucidly as you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.75,0:10:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But there really is nothing to affect me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.09,0:10:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not happier than usual...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.00,0:10:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Munakata struggled, trying to erase that habit off your hands.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.99,0:10:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, did you just say...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.08,0:10:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Munakata was...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.01,0:10:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Munakata Jin was probably \Nwary of this more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.93,0:10:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Athletes whose play depends on the state of their mind \Ncan play like true geniuses while they're happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.45,0:11:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but when they feel bad, they play like beginners.{literal would be 'below beginners' but I don't see a way to shoehorn it here without tearing the CPS apart}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.06,0:11:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.66,0:11:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever wonderful things are happening to you now, \Nput them aside.{/ set your priorities straight.}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.91,0:11:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Put aside?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.30,0:11:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.46,0:11:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiromi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.48,0:11:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.20,0:11:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ozaki and Chiba are here today. \NI came to ask if you would like to dine with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.43,0:11:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure! With pleasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.98,0:11:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Chiba, Ozaki, \Nthat Chinese restaurant was really something.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.17,0:11:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for the treat!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.54,0:11:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevermind. Ozaki's idea. Every once in a while \Nwe should somehow materialize our support.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.41,0:11:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Since I had to miss the Tokyo Cup myself, \NI will at least encourage the rest of Nishi High - you two.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.51,0:12:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't you also encourage Todo in New York?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.24,0:12:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, it was Todo who I wanted to talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.26,0:12:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A summary returned from my New York acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.19,0:12:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Todo's first match:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.73,0:12:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,6-1, 6-2, 6-0.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.23,0:12:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A shutout victory. I had no doubt Todo...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.23,0:12:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Todo has been crushed miserably.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.72,0:12:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It was raining on the court, \Nso only about fifty spectators attended.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.22,0:12:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,His opponent was the rising pro \Nplaced 300th in the rankings.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.18,0:12:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But Todo's arms and legs seemed to have failed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.69,0:12:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The match was a preliminary for preliminary.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.24,0:13:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But for Japan Open Champion Todo, the wall behind which \Nis the world turned out to be too thick and high.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.63,0:13:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to believe it.\NBut the facts I have attest to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.64,0:13:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What is in this fellow Todo's head now? \NAnd how should we think of this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.62,0:13:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,He is a seasoned player. He still has options. \NHe is used to challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.96,0:13:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Even if he goes down once or twice, \Nit does not mean he lost everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.93,0:13:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The final one point...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.43,0:13:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Until it's scored, victory is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.41,0:13:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So he unleashes his fighting spirit, \Nchasing the ball further.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.86,0:13:43.15,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the moment the match is declared finished, \Nhe has to leave the court meekly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.15,0:13:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if it makes him spill a big involuntary tear, he leaves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.83,0:13:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, what you asserted a few days ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.79,0:14:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You said Todo who has been playing tennis since infancy \Nhas already passed his peak.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.91,0:14:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And that by turning a pro now \Nhe will never be able to stand on the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.54,0:14:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But standing on the top is exactly what Todo aims at...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.20,0:14:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it is all happening \Nin precise accordance to your words.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.07,0:14:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you to get me wrong, Hiromi. \NIn fact, I was just... I was just speaking on my account. {/ telling how it would have happened to me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.14,0:14:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sure that for Todo \Nit would be no different than for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.11,0:14:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But it does not mean he should give up surmounting that wall \Nby turning pro and challenging the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.94,0:14:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, he is tenfold more courageous than I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.48,0:14:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry. \NHe'll figure something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.04,0:14:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not about winning or losing,\Nbut rather him tackling whatever is tormenting him. {/ but rather him finding the good answers in his own way.}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.68,0:14:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tackling it...{\i0} {/ Good answers...}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.04,0:14:54.52,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. He embarked on this path \Nnot for anyone else, but for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.31,0:15:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing would offend him more right now \Nthan sympathy and pity.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.96,0:15:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I will say just one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.43,0:15:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Your today's opponent is younger than you. \NA second-year high school student.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.41,0:15:30.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In consequence of her junior success, this match will become \Nher first ever in a major All-Japan tournament.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.89,0:15:34.40,Default,,0,0,10,,{\an8\b0\fnVerdana}Oka Hiromi\N-vs-\NSekiguchi Namiko
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.89,0:15:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That alone would make her \Ncapitalize frantically on your every fault. {This is a clusterfuck of some dialect, half-guessed}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.40,0:15:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You should by no means lose your spirit.\NLet your guard down and she'll attack with everything at once. {/ The game should be the only thing on your mind today.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.60,0:15:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.11,0:15:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.01,0:15:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, I'm sorry. I do my utmost to keep my spirits high, \Nbut it just keeps getting worse! {/ but I just can't help it!}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.53,0:16:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning I received the second letter from Todo.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.81,0:16:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Todo composed it when his first major match in America \Nwas already concluded.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.71,0:16:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in that letter he didn't write a word \Nabout this devastating game.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.30,0:16:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so frustrating. He could just say, \N"I'll do my best next time!" and I'd be perfectly carefree!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.54,0:16:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But instead, all he wrote was how much he cares about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.72,0:16:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, how are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.65,0:16:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time you receive this letter, \Nyour Tokyo Cup matches will surely be in full swing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.24,0:16:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though I'm seeing you \Nrunning around the court with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.46,0:16:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I still remember your powerful serve, \Nyour springy killer smash.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.16,0:16:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, those incredible aces \Nthat always make you smile when scored.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.17,0:17:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Game! One game to three.\NSekiguchi lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.17,0:17:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, Oka,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.46,0:17:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you will triumph brilliantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.60,0:17:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore I expect a delighted reply from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.66,0:17:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, Oka.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.17,0:17:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The autumn comes rushing to New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.30,0:17:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In a blink of an eye, Central Park lost all of its greenery, \Nand the wind has become cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.81,0:17:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In just two more weeks, I believe, the falling leaves \Nwill start dancing their way to the ground. Until then, see you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.65,0:17:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That one last point. \NUntil it is scored, the victory is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.75,0:17:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So he unleashes his fighting spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.23,0:17:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,chasing the ball further.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.65,0:18:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the moment the match is declared over,\Nas he stands there stock-still on the court, involuntarily...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.42,0:18:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.52,0:18:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,at that moment, as he stands on the court stock-still, \Nhe spills a big involuntary tear, I believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.44,0:18:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven games to five. Two games to six.\NLove game to six. Two sets to one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.45,0:18:45.92,Default,,0,0,10,,{\an8\b0\fnVerdana}Hiromi\NSekiguchi
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.62,0:18:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Match won by Sekiguchi!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.86,0:19:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, Hiromi? \NIt was supposed to be an easy game.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.61,0:19:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oka, I was hoping to fight through this tournament \Nalongside with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.57,0:19:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.12,0:19:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.62,0:19:25.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Something makes my body so heavy \NI can hardly move it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.77,0:19:29.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so? Get better then. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.16,0:19:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.13,0:19:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Coach, well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.63,0:19:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You are still allowed to enter the second round.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.19,0:19:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This championship uses \Nthe double-elimination rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.06,0:19:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Six days after the first round defeat, \Nthe loser is allowed to play a repechage match.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.44,0:19:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Make sure that in the repechage match \Nyou don't lose miserably like today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.14,0:19:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Only then I'll listen to your excuses.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.66,0:20:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What would offend him most of all now \Nis other's sympathy and pity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.03,0:20:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The autumn is coming to New York at a rapid pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.76,0:20:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The greenery of Central Park \Nlost its color in a blink of an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.04,0:20:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The wind has suddenly become so cold. \NIn just two more weeks, I'm sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.90,0:20:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the falling leaves \Nwill start dancing their way to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.09,0:21:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This is wrong. \NIt's not about sympathy and pity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.75,0:21:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not how it should be!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.31,0:21:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Not this way!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.85,0:21:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,This is wrong, Todo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.37,0:21:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to see you...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.64,0:21:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I so much want to see Todo!
Comment: 0,0:22:11.59,0:22:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{ED START}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.77,0:22:22.52,Default,ed,0,0,0,,There is one song I cannot ever forget
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.52,0:22:28.15,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Still, there's a face I'm willing to forget
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.15,0:22:31.11,Default,ed,0,0,0,,With her feelings mixed up,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.11,0:22:33.99,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Alice got completely lost
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.99,0:22:39.18,Default,ed,0,0,0,,The midst of summer \NBrought her into one tricky love maze
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.50,0:22:46.09,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I want you to hug tightly\NAnd never let go of me,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.09,0:22:51.47,Default,ed,0,0,0,,One scared and timid tiny girl
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.47,0:22:58.35,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I quite remember our very first kiss \NAnd the beginning of all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.93,0:23:04.77,Default,ed,0,0,0,,While birds were singing for us...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.84,0:23:13.96,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I'll take a car and take a lonely trip
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.96,0:23:19.16,Default,ed,0,0,0,,I know it'll bring me \NTo the seashore
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.16,0:23:22.21,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Where only the the sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.21,0:23:25.25,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Dazzlingly bright,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.25,0:23:30.78,Default,ed,0,0,0,,Could witness my long-awaited happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.49,0:23:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Aikawa Maki here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.69,0:23:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything went wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.99,0:23:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Although Hiromi was admitted to the repechage match, \Nshe told Coach Katsura she won't play it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.70,0:23:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,In response, Coach Katsura blurted on Hiromi:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.07,0:23:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,"You should make a decision \Nof what matters to you the most right now!'
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.58,0:23:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What will you do, Hiromi?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.22,0:23:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to go to New York to see Todo?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.12,0:24:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming soon: "No turning back now."
